# ProtScout v0.5.0 ðŸ§­ðŸ§¬

ProtScout finds proteins belonging to a target family using **HMMER (hmmsearch)**, **DIAMOND**, **InterProScan**, and **motif** searches. It supports optional topology (TMHMM/DeepTMHMM) and SignalP checks. The default **inclusive** scoring keeps any protein positive by HMM/InterPro/Pfam/DIAMOND/motif and deduplicates final results.

## Install
```bash
conda create -n protscout python=3.10 && conda activate protscout
conda install -c conda-forge -c bioconda hmmer diamond seqkit deeptmhmm
# InterProScan (large) and SignalP (license-restricted) are optional.
pip install -e .
```

## Environment check
```bash
find-proteins --check-env
```

## Quick usage
```bash
find-proteins   --fasta examples/proteins.demo.faa   --outdir out_run   --hmm examples/PF00201.demo.hmm   --allow-pfam PF00201 --allow-ipr IPR001296   --scoring-mode inclusive
```

## Output
- `all_proteins_annotation.tsv` â€” merged annotations
- `candidates.tsv` â€” final positives (deduplicated)
- `candidates.faa` â€” FASTA of candidates
- `pipeline.log` â€” commands/stdout log

## Notes
- Inclusive mode ignores TM/SignalP/length for inclusion unless you switch to `--scoring-mode thresholded` and provide those filters.
- You can always add `--topology-metadata-only` to force TM/SignalP to be metadata only.
